article_title: Update: Missing 9-year-old found safe at neighborhood library
article_text:
Update at 11:30 a.m.: Officers found Galdin at a library. She is in good condition, police said.

Original post: Dallas police are looking for a 9-year-old girl last seen Friday at her elementary school in southeast Oak Cliff.

Bryanna Gadlin has been missing since 2:50 p.m. Friday, police said.

She was wearing khaki pants and a black short-sleeved shirt at J.N. Ervin Elementary in the 3700 block of Black Oak Drive.

She is 4-foot-7, weighs 70 pounds and has black braided hair.

Anyone with information is asked to call 911 or Dallas police directly at (214) 671-4268.
